Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law authorizes the Housing Division of the Department of Business and Industry
2 to enter into instruments, agreements and other transactions for certain purposes, including:
3 (1) reducing or modifying the amount or duration of any payment, interest rate, spread or
4 similar risk; and (2) lowering the cost of borrowing when used in combination with the
5 issuance or carrying of bonds or investments. (NRS 319.167) Section 1 of this bill requires
6 the Division to establish a pilot program for certain eligible [families, which is defined to
7 include certain single persons or a person and his or her spouse,] borrowers to buy down the
8 interest rate of a 30-year fixed-rate mortgage loan for an owner-occupied residence for such
9 an eligible [family] borrower in this State. Section 1 requires the eligible [family] borrower
10 to: (1) [have obtained or] be in the process of obtaining [a] his or her first mortgage loan on a
11 residence for the eligible [family;] borrower; (2) qualify as a first-time homebuyer; (3) with
12 certain exceptions, have a household income of not more than 160 percent of the median
13 income for the county in this State in which the residence is located; and (4) meet certain
14 underwriting criteria. Section 1 further [provides that an eligible family may apply to]
15 authorizes the Division to establish a process for an eligible borrower to obtain a waiver of
16 the household income requirement . [under certain circumstances.]
17 Section 2 of this bill makes an appropriation to the Division for the purpose of
18 establishing and carrying out the pilot program.

